Join at: https://awesomesocks.club/

An Absolutely Remarkable Thing eBooks are $2.99 everywhere ebooks are sold (not just amazon...but also on amazon.)

node.text:
The educational media industry finds a lot of ways to charge huge amounts of money for content...charging schools, teachers, parents, and students...the effect is always higher barriers to education and less equal access. I've always found that to be counter-productive and even damaging to society. There are ways to make this media accessible to everyone for free, and if it's possible, WE SHOULD DO IT, because it's better for everyone if everyone has access to education.

So Crash Course videos have always been free. But just because something is free doesn't mean it's cheap. I'm not ashamed to say that it's always been a struggle to make Crash Course work financially. 

We got a lot of inquiries this year from venture capitalists who wanted us to take a lot of money from them to convert Crash Course into a company like that, and there were times when it wasn't always easy to say "no" because, honestly, it's hard to run a business this way. I think people outside of the business world assume that, since we reach so many people, we must be making good money, but an average Crash Course costs over half a million dollars to produce, and it's VERY hard to make that up with YouTube ads and Patreon.

We reach over 70 million individual students per year with a budget that's less than what some universities spend on brochures. The Crash Course team does so much, and they want to do more! I've been searching for ways to support them better.

One of the things I know we can do more of...is just ask.

So I'm asking, go to CrashCourseCoin.com and you can get a one-of-a-kind, only-available-this-week-and-then-never-again, minted-in-Arkansas, hand-engraved 2021 Crash Course coin as a very real token of our ability to reach either 2,000 or 10,000 learners. Thanks to everyone who has done it so far, it's going to enable us to do so much good work this year and in coming years.

There’s a link in my bio!!
